	<h1>So what if I play music?</h1>
	<ul>
		<li>A scale in music is a preordained set of notes that you can play, just like using a specific coding language.</li>
		<li>Semantic code structure looks very similar to written music, with organized lines, stacks notes that make up a chord, and stacks of code that make up a function. These functions can then be used to give your code power, just as chords can give music more power.</li>
		<li>Writing code requires strict adherence to the accepted standards, as does writing music. If you deviate from a given key or scale, it will be harder for others to make sense of the music.</li>
	</ul>
	<h2>The passion that I bring to music is the same passion that I bring to coding...</h2>
