		<h4 class="composition_name">Etude No. 3 in Db major "Un Sospiro"</h4>
		<p>Un Sospiro is an etude that studies the crossing of the hands. Its name is Italian for "A sigh". It is also a study in the way that hands should affect the melody, with its many accentuations and phrasing with alternate hands. The piece is quite complex, even utilizing three staves at times. It is widely regarded as one of the most beautiful piano pieces ever composed.</p>
		<p>Not having played it since my recital several years ago, I am trying to bring it back up to snuff and fix some of the rushed phrasing and missed notes that were present in my recital.</p>
