<div class="row musical_piece jeux_deau">
	<div class="holder">
		<h3 class="composition_title">Maurice Ravel - Jeux d'eau</h3>
		<p>Dedicated to Gabriel Faure, Ravel composed this piece in 1901 under the tutelage of Faure. It is a late-romantic and impressionistic work using the whole-tone scale. It is written in sonata form, though it does not conform to the traditional sonata tonal form. It is very technically challenging and requires suppleness of fingers in order to perform the dense orchestration while bringing out a properly phrased melody. Its name is french for "Water play", or "Water fountain". It was written to convey the sounds of water splashing or being sprayed.</p>
		<p>This amazing impressionistic masterpiece is one of my all time favorites. It is unbelievable how Ravel actually makes the piano emulate the sounds of water. Also extremely difficult, I run into issues with my hands not being quite large enough to play some notes simultaneously.</p>
